Classic car fusion is proud to offer this pristine 1968 Camaro RS Z/28.  With only 7,199 Z28s built in 1968, and with roughly 17% of all Camaros receiving the RS package that year, means this car is one of roughly 1200 made. This is a numbers matching car with its original 302ci motor (engine stamp V0418M0) that has gone through a complete frame off restoration.  The motor and transmission were recently rebuilt, it has a period correct Muncie 4 speed, and what we believe to be the original 3:73 posi 12 bolt rear end.  She was originally british green , and has been tastefully upgraded to Matador red with white stripes.  This Z also sports a deluxe interior and console gauges.  This is a true investment quality 68 RS Z/28 that runs and drives great.
